videos.headline: Jackson uses defender to get the first
videos.description: Louisville's Lamar Jackson uses the Clemson defender to get extra yards for the first down.

videos.headline: Bryant goes long on first drive
videos.description: Clemson's Kelly Bryant airs it deep to Hunter Renfrow for the 40-yard completion on the Tigers first drive.

videos.headline: Bryant keeps it for the first TD
videos.description: Clemson's Kelly Bryant keeps the ball and runs 8 yards into the end zone to give the Tigers the first touchdown of the game against Louisville.

videos.headline: Jackson splits defenders for huge gain
videos.description: Louisville's Lamar Jackson splits the defenders and surges downfield for the 30-yard run.

videos.headline: Clemson defender ejected for targeting
videos.description: Clemson's Tanner Muse is ejected for targeting on a tackle with Louisville's Lamar Jackson.

videos.headline: Jackson helps Louisville's offense
videos.description: Louisville's Lamar Jackson uses his feet to extend the play and finds Charles Standberry in the end zone to tie the Tigers at 7-7.

videos.headline: Bryant airs it deep for the long TD
videos.description: Clemson's Kelly Bryant throws it downfield for Ray-Ray McCloud for the 79-yard touchdown to give the Tigers the 16-7 lead, after the PAT is blocked.

videos.headline: Petrino discusses 'frustrated' Jackson
videos.description: Louisville coach Bobby Petrino acknowledges quarterback Lamar Jackson's struggles against Clemson going into halftime.

videos.headline: Clemson in control at the half
videos.description: Kelly Bryant throws a touchdown and runs for a score to lead Clemson to a first half lead over conference rival Louisville.

videos.headline: Jackson throws pick-six
videos.description: Louisville's Lamar Jackson continues to struggle against Clemson's defense as he throws an interception that is returned for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Feaster almost gets into the end zone
videos.description: Clemson's Tavien Feaster runs for a 26-yard gain, but the Louisville defender is there for the touchdown saving tackle.

videos.headline: Clemson 'hammers a nail in the coffin'
videos.description: Clemson's Kelly Bryant gets into the end zone untouched as the Tigers start to pull away from Louisville late in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Clemson allows first second-half points of season
videos.description: Louisville's Lamar Jackson finds a wide-open Jaylen Smith in the end zone to put up the first points against Clemson in a second half this season.

videos.headline: Clemson makes the right Choice for the TD
videos.description: Clemson's Adam Choice dances into the end zone with the 39-yard run to give the Tigers the 40-14 lead over Louisville.

videos.headline: Williams gets airborne after the catch
videos.description: Louisville's Malik Williams leaps over the defender to finish a 11-yard catch.

videos.headline: Jackson extends play to score TD
videos.description: Louisville's Lamar Jackson extends the play with his feet and finds Dez Fitzpatrick at the edge of the end zone for the touchdown.

videos.headline: Clemson breaks away with the TD
videos.description: Clemson's Travis Etienne sheds defenders and runs 81 yards for the touchdown to pad the lead for the Tigers in the fourth quarter.

videos.headline: Clemson too much for Jackson, Louisville
videos.description: Kelly Bryant leads Clemson's rout of Louisville with 316 yards and one touchdown in the air and two scores on the ground in a 47-21 win.

videos.headline: Clemson rolls against Louisville
videos.description: No. 3 Clemson records 613 total yards and cashes a pick-six off of Lamar Jackson in a 47-21 win over No. 14 Louisville.
